name: Crn Bread
text: The WORST company to work for in the state! Supervisor Reneita is very unprofessional! You receive no training because people feel like it's not their job to train you since they're not getting paid for it! They are so SORRY that they dont even show you where the bathroom is located nor do they show you where the time clock is at! Extreme heat conditions that you have to work in. Coworkers are rude, liars, keep up drama and gossip all day! The job itself is easy but the staff is awful! Huge turnover and I now see why they cant keep people to work there! And it's only $10hr which no one should have to deal with such nonsense with so little pay and foolishness in the workplace! I wouldn't recommend a dog to go there EVER!

name: Bryan Carter
text: Publisher of the highest respected publication in their industry. Professional is the best word to describe Hatton-Brown Publishers. They take pride in their work, are dedicated to excellence and possess a loyalty to their readers that has long since gone out of style. I've worked closely with Hatton-Brown Publishers for over 20 years and they've become like family. You will benefit from doing business with such a company — my business has. Ask for Dianne!
